dc_title_s: Middlesex County, New Jersey, during American Revolution verso
dc_description_s: Verso of a map of the County of Middlesex in the Province of New Jersey during the American Revolution compiled by John E. Brush of the Rutgers University Department of Geography for the Middlesex County Cultural and Heritage Commission. Features table of populations of each township and tax ratables as of 1782 at top followed by a history of the political division of the county and finally, nine lithographed illustrations and descriptions of historical buildings and landmarks.
